  "recommendation": {
    "suitable_as_master": true|false,
    "reasoning": "Brief explanation of scoring"
  }
}
```

## Scoring Criteria

### Breadth Score (0.0 - 1.0)
- 1.0 = Covers ALL taxonomy sections
- 0.5 = Covers ~50% of taxonomy sections
- 0.0 = Covers almost no taxonomy sections

### Depth Score (0.0 - 1.0)
- 1.0 = All covered sections have comprehensive, detailed content
- 0.5 = Mix of detailed and shallow coverage
- 0.0 = All coverage is superficial/mentioned only

### Unique Content Score (0.0 - 1.0)
- 1.0 = Contains significant unique content not in taxonomy
- 0.5 = Some unique content
- 0.0 = No content outside taxonomy

### Overall Score (weighted combination)
`overall = (breadth × 0.4) + (depth × 0.4) + (unique × 0.2)`

## Rules
- DO NOT read the entire document word-for-word; skim for structure and coverage
- DO note specific section IDs from the taxonomy
- DO identify gaps explicitly
- DO provide honest assessment even if coverage is poor
